{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"9e026170-d19e-407c-a499-749e160f9eb0","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/resume-worktree-reconciliation/ for the halt→resume worktree-reconciliation feature.\n\nDesign summary:\n- New module src/core/resume/reconcile-worktree.ts with a pure classifier isReconcilableArtifact() and an I/O orchestrator reconcileWorktreeArtifacts(). Reconcile runs in ResumeCommand.prepare() after the (unchanged) apply-canon gate, inside the same worktree guard, so it covers default / --from / --apply-canon paths.\n- 3-class recovery contract: (1) protected canon → unchanged apply-canon gate; (2) pipeline-managed artifact (under change folder ∧ ¬protectedCanonPaths ∧ ¬pipelineManagedPaths) → quarantine to .specrunner/local/<slug>/ then remove, quarantine failure is fail-closed; (3) non-managed (src/ + the state journal state.json/events.jsonl/usage.json) → untouched. Reuses pipelineManagedPaths as the keep-set to avoid drift and to protect the just-written running-state journal.\n- Quarantine-all-then-remove-all (evidence never lost); removal split by tracked state mirrors restoreViolatedPaths; detection is best-effort no-op while quarantine/removal is fail-closed (D7), which also keeps existing apply-canon tests green unchanged.\n\nAll 6 acceptance criteria are mapped to tasks (T-05 TC-R1 walks the real findScopedCommitViolations/findWriteScopeViolations halt path; T-05 TC-R2 quarantine-failure fail-closed; T-05 TC-R3 idempotent no-op; T-08 apply-canon unchanged-green; T-03+T-07 docs contract+drift-guard; T-09 typecheck && test). Scope-outs honored (no write-set-check change, no halt-side cleanup, non-managed dirt behavior preserved). No source edits performed — planning only.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-23T09:15:52.792Z","endedAt":"2026-07-23T09:29:45.028Z","commitOid":"0d929abd3f537cb727382f4a5ed6d78e2f5d702c"}
